272
00:16:15.200 --> 00:16:19.070
And then finally, we try the best we can

273
00:16:19.120 --> 00:16:22.200
to use existing evidence-based interventions

274
00:16:23.380 --> 00:16:26.349
because, again, we don't want to take it away when the study's over.

275
00:16:26.730 --> 00:16:30.660
So, for example, when we're addressing tobacco use, we partner with the state

276
00:16:30.800 --> 00:16:34.480
quit line because they'll provide free treatment and free

277
00:16:34.520 --> 00:16:38.340
cessation meds. We partner with the state's breast and cervical cancer

278
00:16:38.440 --> 00:16:38.880
program,

279
00:16:40.660 --> 00:16:43.180
with diabetes prevention programs, et cetera.

280
00:16:43.320 --> 00:16:46.940
So we use existing EBIs to work with

281
00:16:47.060 --> 00:16:49.680
them because those things will be there when the grant's over.

282
00:16:52.160 --> 00:16:54.979
So we've been unbelievably successful.

283
00:16:55.140 --> 00:16:58.450
We're now serving over 20 PIs

284
00:16:59.160 --> 00:17:02.760
at Utah and the Huntsman Cancer Institute.

285
00:17:02.860 --> 00:17:06.181
We've got about 55 million in funding in the last nine

